Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Trim the @aubergine{1} and cut into 2cm pieces then pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over the @chermoula spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Pop the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams} onto a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Place the tomato parcel onto the aubergine baking tray.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{17-18%minutes}. Turn the aubergine halfway through.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} to the pan. Fry until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Cover and set aside for now.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks and pop onto another baking tray. Drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until golden, ~{6-8%minutes}. Once golden, remove from the oven and set aside.

While the croutons bake, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium frying pan on medium heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%secs}.

Add the lentils to the pan and stir together until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When ready, add the lentils, roasted aubergine and tomatoes to the dressing and toss to coat.

Allow to sit for ~{1%minute} to absorb the flavours.

Just before serving, mix the @baby leaf mix{50%grams} and croutons into your salad, then share between your bowls.

Top with the cooked chicken, crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%grams} over and drizzle on the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams}. Enjoy!